properties.headline: Lake Wind Advisory issued January 20 at 2:22PM PST until January 21 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 40 mph
expected. Waves 2 to 4 feet.

* WHERE...Lake Tahoe. Highest waves from mid lake to northeast
shores.

* WHEN...From 4 AM to 10 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Small boats, kayaks and paddle boards will be prone
to capsizing and should remain off lake waters until
conditions improve.
properties.instruction:
Check lake conditions before heading out and be prepared for a
sudden increase in winds and wave heights. Consider postponing
boating activities on the lake until a day with less wind.

NWSheadline: LAKE WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM TO 10 PM PST TUESDAY FOR LAKE TAHOE
